 need to make __ptr_pu and __ret_pu<br />&gt; explicitly "%"_ASM_CX".<br /><br />No, the "c"/"0" thing is much better, and makes it properly atomic wrt<br />the actual asm.<br /><br />As mentioned to Andy, the "register asm()" thing is not uncommon and<br />often useful, but when you can specify the register directly in asm,<br />that's certainly simpler and more straightforward and preferred.<br /><br />              Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
